          <strong>What are Canaries?</strong>
          <p style="margin: 10px 0 0 0;">Canaries are automated tests that run on a schedule to monitor your endpoints and workflows. They catch issues before your users do by continuously validating that your application is working as expected.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Common Canary Use Cases</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Endpoint monitoring</strong>: Check that your API endpoints respond correctly</li>
          <li><strong>Page load testing</strong>: Verify websites load within acceptable time</li>
          <li><strong>User workflow testing</strong>: Test complete user journeys (login, checkout, etc.)</li>
          <li><strong>SSL certificate monitoring</strong>: Alert before certificates expire</li>
        </ul>

